title: Grateful Dead Live at Robert F. Kennedy Stadium on 1989-07-13
lineage: Master DAT @ 48kHz > Panasonic SV3700  > 48kHz 16bit Wav > Sample Manager > 44.1kHz 24bit Wav > Wavelab 8.5 / Izotope Ozone 6.1 / MBit+ Dither > 44.1kHz 16bit wav; Recorded, Transferred and Digitally Mastered by Dan Tepper
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, Cold Rain & Snow, Little Red Rooster, Tennessee Jed*, Memphis Blues*, To Lay Me Down, Let It Grow

Set 2

He's Gone-> Looks Like Rain, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> I Will Take You Home-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

* Bruce Hornsby, accordion *

reviews.review_text: Nice sound Haven't listened to much of the show yet, but had to add a compliment to the taper since this show doesn't have any reviews yet. This is a really nice, lush AUD. Some sort of minor dispute is captured at the beginning of Terrapin... kinda funny, though I can't quite make out what they're saying.
